description: Has Thor turned his back on Asgard? Has Asgard turned it's back on Thor?! After a series of monumental and cataclysmic events, the God of Thunder' life has changed completley! What unexpected way do his true friends figure out to help him? And what could possibly be the next step in the devious Loki's sinister scheme and machinations? Then in Thor: Giant Size Finale, treacherous plans for the Asgardians in thier new home of Latveria...and does the scheming Dr. Doom have an agenda of Doom's own? Collecting THOR #601-603 and THOR: GIANT SIZE FINALE.

description:
1. Dangerous Deception - Poor Linda Crane from the wrong side of the tracks cheats and lies her way into the glamorous world of interior decorating, only to discover it was love she wanted all along, not a career.

2. Romance Cottage - Real estate agent sells a house to a misogynist, tames him.

3. Love Under A Cloud - Della Morris from Coalburg longs to escape her dirty town and arranged marriage when a city slicker almost seduces her into leaving; but the mine collapses and she realizes she really does love Big Jim the coal miner, and really doesn't mind spending the rest of her life in the quaint little town.

4. My Love Confessions - prose short story.

5. Tempest in the Timber - This idyllic story features Rusty Rourke, all-round tomboy and daughter of the owner of the logging company. Rusty's too tough to fall for any man until she meets Dave the forest ranger; but the sinister Mike the lumberjack has other ideas. Luck and pluck let the two young lovers escape the evil lumberjack's machinations culminating in an exciting fistfight between Mike and the ranger - the happy couple promise to "grow old together among the ancient trees."
name: Dangerous Deception

description:
1. My Steady's Other Girl - Two women engaged to the same man accidentally meet. 

 2.  We Were Meant For Each Other - Former girlfriend tries to sabotage ex's new relationship.
 
3. Which Path Is Mine? - Girl tries to decide between love and security.
 
4. Foolish Fancy - Short story
 
5. My Shameless Vanity - Self centered girl loses beau and then mends ways to convince him to take her back.
name: My Shameless Vanity

description:
1. Who Am I?  - Amnesia victim fends off true- romance when she discovers she was previously engaged.
 
2. Trust in Me - Fashion model's jealous boyfriend causes problems.
 
3. I Wanted a He-Man - Shallow woman spurns true love because he can't swim, play tennis or ride horses; but is proved wrong in the end, much to her regret and shame.
 
4. The Heiress - short story.
 
5. Too Anxious to Marry - Woman goes behind fiance's back to help him with business deal, only to be taken advantage of.  Fiance forgives her and all turns out well as she resolves to stay in the kitchen from now on.
name: Who Am I?

description:
In TRUE BELIEVERS, it's an all-new beginning for the book that Wizard calls 'the best original concept from Marvel in thirty years!' When a group of teenagers discovers that their parents are actually super-villains, they run away from home...but that's only step one! Now that the evil Pride is gone, nearly every bad guy in the Marvel Universe is trying to fill the power vacuum in Los Angeles, and the Runaways are the only heroes who can stop them! Plus: What does a mysterious new team of young heroes want with the Runaways, and which fan-favorite Marvel characters are part of this group? And in ESCAPE TO NEW YORK, the Runaways embark on a coast-to-coast adventure, guest-starring Cloak and Dagger AND the New Avengers! When Cloak is accused of a crime he didn't commit by the heroes of New York City, the vigilante is forced to turn to the teenage Runaways for help. This story will take our teens to a place they've never been: NYC!

Collects Runaways 1-12 and the Runaways/X-Men team-up from FREE COMIC BOOK DAY 2006, plus extras.
name: Volume 2

description:
Created and written by Harvey and Eagle Award-nominated writer Dwight L. MacPherson, illustrated and lettered by animator and artist Igor Noronha.  
 
When teenage genius Adam Graham traveled back in time to Edwardian London, he never dreamed he'd be fighting for his life against steam-powered robots, science-sorcerers, a demonic state assassin and a dead queen's brain!
name: SIDEWISE

description: Logan has been trained to kill; born and bred from conception to be the best of the best, but his time is short, he’s nearing the end of his life. Age 21, when every citizen reports for Deep Sleep. But before his life ends he’s got one final mission: Find and destroy Sanctuary, a fabled haven for those that chose to defy the system. William F. Nolan’s masterpiece of dystopian future once again races into the 23 Century with this all-new Graphic Novel adaptation of LOGAN’S RUN. When Last Day comes, will you lie down and die…or run!
name: Logan's Run: Lastday

description: Working as a private dick is weird business, no matter how you look at it. But working as a private dick in a world populated by ghouls, monsters and other creatures of the night? well, that's as weird as it gets. Welcome to the world of Cal McDonald. When a bizarre string of strangulation murders hits the streets of Los Angeles, and the bodies are found covered in blood, at first it seems like a madman is on the loose. But when it's revealed that the blood isn't from the victims and in fact, it's not even of human origin Cal sets his sights on a rendering warehouse close to where the bodies were found. 30 Days of Night creators Niles and Templesmith give whole new meaning to the phrase Meat Is Murder.
name: Love Me Tenderloin: A Cal McDonald Mystery

description:
Eat the Press

Your source for scare and unbalanced news! In the wake of 'Ba-rot' Obama's assault on the undead presidents, the survivors are reeling and the press want answers! With the government and military in tatters, Bill O'Smiley and Crush Limbo take to the airwaves and declare themselves de facto leaders of the people. Now the C-I-C of an army of zombies, will Obama use his trump card to bring peace at last, or will he plunge us into a true American nightmare?
name: Eat The Press
